                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In telegram 438, April 14, 1:51 p. m., from New York, Mr. Ross sent to Mr. Rusk
                    the informal, written comments of the Jewish Agency <pb facs="0310" n="820"
                        xml:id="pg_820"/> on the American 15-point trusteeship program for
                    Palestine. The telegram noted that Mr. Ross had received the comments the night
                    before. At one point in the 14-page telegram, appeared the following Jewish
                    Agency comment: “It is because the very concept of trusteeship is so flagrantly
                    out of accord with the general principles and current realities of the Palestine
                    situation that no improvement of the US proposals can make them a useful
                    starting point in the quest for a political settlement.” (501.BB
                    Palestine/4–1448)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
